PN,31702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776038571
OL,3,CExpert teams to be sent to hospitals
OL,4,Cwith highest rates of corridor care
OL,6,FIt comes as the Department of Health
OL,7,Fand Social Care (DHSC) revealed the
OL,8,Flocations of 40 new and expanded same-
OL,9,Fday emergency care and urgent care
OL,10,Fcentres, which will allow patients to
OL,11,Fbe treated faster and ease pressure on
OL,12,FA&Es.
OL,14,FNHS England published its definition
OL,15,Fof corridor care in March. Patients
OL,16,Fspending 45 minutes or more in
OL,17,Fclinically inappropriate areas of
OL,18,Femergency departments or wards, such
OL,19,Fas hallways or waiting rooms, are
OL,20,Fconsidered to have experienced
OL,21,Fcorridor care.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776038571
OL,3,CExpert teams to be sent to hospitals
OL,4,Cwith highest rates of corridor care
OL,6,FTrusts have started collecting data on
OL,7,Fthe practice, which will be published
OL,8,Ffor the first time in May.
OL,10,FLast month, ITV News reported on a
OL,11,Fwoman who lost her husband after he
OL,12,Fspent 36 hours in the "carnage" of an
OL,13,FA&E corridor, while suffering fatal
OL,14,Fswelling of the brain.
OL,16,FTom Frith, 66, from Cheshire, was
OL,17,Frushed to the A&E department at
OL,18,FLeighton Hospital in June 2025,
OL,19,Fsuffering with a temperature,
OL,20,Fconfusion and struggling with his
OL,21,Fspeech.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776038571
OL,3,CExpert teams to be sent to hospitals
OL,4,Cwith highest rates of corridor care
OL,6,F"It was carnage - bodies everywhere
OL,7,Fand nurses running around," Tom's
OL,8,Fwife, Julia Chard, told ITV News.
OL,10,FTom was left in a corridor for 36
OL,11,Fhours, undiagnosed with a serious
OL,12,Fcondition called encephalitis, which
OL,13,Fcauses inflammation of the brain and
OL,14,Frequires urgent medical treatment.
OL,16,FHe was eventually diagnosed a week
OL,17,Fafter he first attended A&E, but due
OL,18,Fto the brain damage which had already
OL,19,Foccurred, Tom never recovered and died
OL,20,Fweeks later.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
